{meta: title Stormy Waters}
{meta: artist Doyle Lawson}
{meta: composer Henry Donohue}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Stormy waters all around me waves are rough and rolling high
But amidst it all (but amidst it all)
I plainly [G7]see (I plainly see)
There's a [C]fairest of all havens and the keeper hears my cry
To the rock of ages (rock of ages)
[G7]Cleft for [C]me (for [F]even [C]me)
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Stormy waters round me (stormy waters round me)
Thunder rolls (loud the thunders roll)
How the mighty billows (how the mighty billows)
Tossed my [G7]soul (tossed my soul)
Lord to [C]find sweet comfort (Lord to find sweet comfort)
When I see (when I look and see)
To the rock of ages (rock of ages)
[G7]Cleft for [C]me (for [F]even [C]me)
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Not a moment spent in slumber restlessly I sail along
Then my Savior dear (then my Savior dear)
Hears myself [G7]plead (hears myself plead)
Soon the [C]ocean waves are peaceful and my heart breaks forth in song
To the rock of ages (rock of ages)
[G7]Cleft for [C]me (for [F]even [C]me)
{end_of_verse}

